POLICE are looking for eight suspects who allegedly bombed two ATMs and robbed a petrol station of cigarettes and money. The incident happened in the early hours of Thursday morning, 28 July in Evaton North, Vaal. Sipho Skhosana (38), who lives near the petrol station, said at about 1am, he heard a loud bang followed by another five explosions. Gauteng police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Mavela Masondo said eight men, some armed, stormed into the BP station and held employees and a customer at gunpoint. The men then bombed two ATMs at the petrol station and took an undisclosed amount of cash before hijacking a Toyota Quantum, which they used to flee. He said no shots were fired and no injuries were reported. The hijacked Quantum was later found abandoned in the area. Cops opened cases of ATM bombing, business robbery and car hijacking.